following.

00:00:29.830 --> 00:00:35.624
They said, "You've written
a wave function ψ(x) and

00:00:35.624 --> 00:00:37.000
A(p).
 

00:00:37.000 --> 00:00:41.077
There seems to be no reference
of time, so where is time in

00:00:41.077 --> 00:00:44.100
this," and they couldn't
stop there.

00:00:44.100 --> 00:00:47.070
That would be a good place to
stop but they went on to say,

00:00:47.070 --> 00:00:50.637
"Are you saying the ψ
is just a ψ

00:00:50.637 --> 00:00:52.540
as time goes by?"
 

00:00:52.540 --> 00:00:55.110
So that's the kind of stuff
that appeals to me,

00:00:55.110 --> 00:00:58.060
so I don't care if you don't
learn any quantum mechanics,

00:00:58.060 --> 00:01:02.590
